"{\"uid\": \"dominicantoday.com-dr-people-2024-08-12-dominican-olympic-champions-return\", \"text\": \"HOMEABOUT USADVERTISINGCONTACT  Last update on December 2, 2025, 1:58 pm  PeopleAugust 12, 2024 | 8:18 am  Text size:SmallerBigger  Image: N Digital  Santo Domingo.-Marileidy Paulino, along with boxers Yunior Alc\\u00e1ntara and Cristian Pinales, who all medaled at the XXXIII Olympic Games in Paris 2024, returned to the Dominican Republic on Sunday afternoon and were welcomed as national heroes.  Las Am\\u00e9ricas International Airport (AILA) was filled with supporters, many of whom traveled from Paulino's hometown of Nizao to celebrate her homecoming.  Paulino, the Dominican Republic's sole gold medalist at Paris 2024, was joined by bronze medalists Alc\\u00e1ntara and Pinales as they greeted well-wishers and travelers at the terminal.  The government organized a special reception for the three athletes, who returned ahead of the conclusion of the XXXIII Olympic Games.  Thanks to Paulino's gold medal and the two bronze medals won by Alc\\u00e1ntara and Pinales, the Dominican Republic ranked 59th in the overall medal standings.  Marileidy Paulino also set a new Olympic record in the 400-meter track and field event, finishing with a time of 48.17 seconds.    \\u0394    \\u0394  MI NEGRA!  esta muy bien por toda pais,  I thought there were no \\\"true dominicans\\\" with that look.    November 30, 2025 | 11:21 am  November 29, 2025 | 9:00 am  November 28, 2025 | 11:01 am  November 23, 2025 | 11:09 am  November 21, 2025 | 2:27 pm  November 16, 2025 | 7:00 am  Tourism  Health  Expats' Corner  People  People  World  Sports  Local  DominicanToday.com- The Dominican Republic News Source in English  Av. Abraham Lincoln N\\u00b0 452 Local 220B, Plaza La Francesa, Piantini, Santo Domingo  Tel. (809) 334-6386\"}"